## Run: api-pod-kill — <date> <HH:MM TZ>
**Environment:** staging
**Duration:** 5m
**Operator:** <name>

### Hypothesis
<paste from experiment plan>

### Result: PASS / FAIL

### Metrics
<paste comparison table>

### Observations
- <what happened, in plain language>
- <anything surprising — even on a PASS>

### Action items
- [ ] <ticket reference + owner>
- [ ] <follow-up experiment, if any>

### Decisions
- Promote experiment to weekly scheduled run? Y/N
- Promote experiment to production game day? Y/N (only if 3 consecutive
  PASS runs in staging)
```

### Step 9: Production guardrails (only if user asks)

Prod runs require ALL of:

1. **Three consecutive PASS in staging** for the same experiment.
2. **`prod=true`** explicitly in the experiment manifest annotations.
3. **Blast-radius limits**: target one pod, one zone, one tenant — never all.
4. **Active operator** at the keyboard — never scheduled chaos in prod
   without a human on standby.
5. **Auto-abort hook**: a watchdog that kills the experiment when SLO
   burn-rate alert fires. Generate:

```yaml
apiVersion: chaos-mesh.org/v1alpha1
kind: Workflow
metadata: { name: api-pod-kill-with-watchdog, namespace: chaos-prod }
spec:
  entry: parallel
  templates:
    - name: parallel
      templateType: Parallel
      children: [kill, watchdog]
    - name: kill
      templateType: PodChaos
      podChaos: { action: pod-kill, mode: one, duration: "2m", selector: { ... } }
    - name: watchdog
      templateType: Task
      task:
        container:
          image: gstack/chaos-watchdog:latest
          env:
            - { name: ABORT_ON_ALERT, value: "<service>SLOFastBurn" }
            - { name: ABORT_ACTION, value: "kubectl delete podchaos/api-pod-kill" }
```

6. **AskUserQuestion gate** at run time: "Confirm prod chaos run? Y/N"
   — agent does NOT auto-execute.

